It apparently occurred due to a fight which started at a local tavern. It is believed that the suspect was called a &#8220;Shangaan from Stoffberg&#8221;.He became angry and unleashed deadly force onto the man, before the body was dumped.It was discovered a few hours later by someone who wanted to use the bathroom and police were alerted.The suspect was arrested and has been identified as Ephraim Mokwena. He was meant to appear in court last week but was apparently assaulted in custody.Police said that the man was taken to hospital for treatment and will make another appearance before court on charges of murder this week. The family of the deceased are yet to identify his body.